ash-chain verification\n- `BufferedEntry` (lines 93-102) - Internal buffered entry before flush\n- `AuditWriteError` (lines 46-55) - Error thrown when audit persistence fails\n\n### Key Architectural Points\n\n1. **Buffering Strategy**: Audit entries are buffered in memory and auto-flushed every 100ms or at 50 entries, reducing database round-trips\n2. **Hash-Chain Integrity**: SHA-256 chain ensures audit trail cannot be modified without detection\n3. **Event-Driven**: AuditPolicy uses event emitters for automatic audit logging without manual instrumentation\n4. **Retention Policy**: Separate policy class enforces compliance constraints (minimum 90 days)\n5. **Error Handling**: Audit logging failures are caught and logged but never crash the application\n\nAll files mentioned above are available at the absolute paths shown (using Windows forward slashes in paths like `C:\\Users\\kazda\\kiro\\personas-cloud\\packages\\...`)."}],"totalDurationMs":51538,"totalTokens":44681,"totalToolUseCount":18,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":257,"cache_read_input_tokens":42806,"output_tokens":1615,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":257},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
